Compilation flags:
========================================
Enable : MODEL=HYDRO, GRAVITY, GREP, EOS=GAMMA, NLEVEL=4
Disable:

Default setup:
========================================
1. Enable external potential
   --> OPT__EXT_POT = 3
2. Maximum refinement level (MAX_LEVEL) = 3 or modify the Input_Flag_Rho
3. Use Gamma-law EoS
   --> GAMMA = 2.0, K = 1.455e5 (cgs)

Note:
========================================
1. A test problem for neutron star migration test
   --> initial condition `tovstar_short` is generated by solving TOV equation

2. The GREP is treated as external potential.
   --> the following function pointers in test problem will be overrided,
       and are automatically rebinded to

      Init_ExtPot_Ptr               = Init_ExtPot_GREP;
      Poi_UserWorkBeforePoisson_Ptr = Poi_UserWorkBeforePoisson_GREP;
      End_ExtPot_Ptr                = End_ExtPot_GREP;

3. If `GAMER_DEBUG` compilation flag is enabled, additional information will be output
   to standard output for debugging the constructed GREP
   --> see src/SelfGravity/CPU_Poisson/CPU_ComputeGREP.cpp for detail

4. The central density is recorded in Record__CentralDens
